00:06:37.050 --> 00:06:41.350
A few more fun facts about Venus.

00:06:41.350 --> 00:06:45.870
As a starting point, Venus is
almost the same size as Earth.

00:06:45.870 --> 00:06:49.080
This is one of the reasons
why we find it so fascinating

00:06:49.080 --> 00:06:53.090
because it starts out, you think,
well, it's about 85% the size

00:06:53.090 --> 00:06:57.390
of Earth, it's about 90% of it's
mass, about 90% of it's gravity,

00:06:57.390 --> 00:07:02.410
but right there is about where the
similarities end and things start

00:07:02.410 --> 00:07:05.310 position:56%
to be a little different from Earth.

00:07:05.310 --> 00:07:11.510
Another fun fact, the Venus day
is longer than the Venus year.

00:07:11.510 --> 00:07:16.120
What that means is that when Venus
rotates on its axis one time,

00:07:16.120 --> 00:07:19.130
it takes longer for it to
rotate on its axis than it takes

00:07:19.130 --> 00:07:23.710 position:56%
to go all the way around the Sun, to
make that whole trip around the Sun.

00:07:23.710 --> 00:07:29.700
And because Venus rotates so
slowly, it's almost spherical.

00:07:29.700 --> 00:07:33.240
It's different from Earth and Mars,
which rotate, in a relative sense,

00:07:33.240 --> 00:07:35.550
faster than Venus anyway.

00:07:35.550 --> 00:07:36.850
And they're most oblate.

00:07:36.850 --> 00:07:38.670
They're kind of squashed
because they spin so fast

00:07:38.670 --> 00:07:40.520 position:56%
that they spread out at the equator.

00:07:40.520 --> 00:07:41.820
Well, Venus doesn't do that.

00:07:41.820 --> 00:07:44.030
It's almost exactly spherical.

00:07:44.030 --> 00:07:47.150
It also rotates backwards.

00:07:47.150 --> 00:07:50.300
It rotates retrograde.

00:07:50.300 --> 00:07:52.690
Why? We don't know.

00:07:52.690 --> 00:07:54.520
It could be, some people
have suggested

00:07:54.520 --> 00:07:58.750
that maybe Venus rotates backwards,
because maybe it was hit sometime

00:07:58.750 --> 00:08:02.960
in its early history by a giant
asteroid, a giant impacter,

00:08:02.960 --> 00:08:04.810
and that caused Venus to slow down

00:08:04.810 --> 00:08:06.770
and perhaps begin rotating
backwards.

00:08:06.770 --> 00:08:09.960
But there's also other
hypotheses, other suggestions

00:08:09.960 --> 00:08:13.990
that maybe there's just some
probability of 10 to 20%

00:08:13.990 --> 00:08:16.100
that you're going to
get 1 in 8 or 9 planets

00:08:16.100 --> 00:08:17.890
that rotates the other direction.

00:08:17.890 --> 00:08:20.240
So we don't really know the
answer to that question.

00:08:20.240 --> 00:08:24.040
It's a pretty important outstanding
question about how planets form

00:08:24.040 --> 00:08:27.560
and how they spin up in
their original state.

00:08:27.560 --> 00:08:31.020
Venus also has its axis
pointing straight up and down.

00:08:31.020 --> 00:08:32.800
You know how Earth were on a tilt?

00:08:32.800 --> 00:08:35.510
And as we travel around the
Sun, because we're on that tilt,

00:08:35.510 --> 00:08:38.560
that's why we have seasons,
different temperatures

00:08:38.560 --> 00:08:41.190
and different climates in
different parties of the year.

00:08:41.190 --> 00:08:45.360
Well, at Venus, that axis, that
spin axis, is straight up and down.

00:08:45.360 --> 00:08:48.560
And so there's no seasons on Venus.

00:08:48.560 --> 00:08:52.770
In addition to not having
seasons, the atmosphere

00:08:52.770 --> 00:08:56.920
on Venus is incredibly
thick and dense.

00:08:56.920 --> 00:08:59.690
So you almost have no
difference between day and night,

00:08:59.690 --> 00:09:01.810
as far as what it's like on
the surface of the planet,

00:09:01.810 --> 00:09:03.980
other than the amount of
lighting that's available.

00:09:03.980 --> 00:09:06.610
But even that's not much different.

00:09:06.610 --> 00:09:12.620
The atmosphere on Venus is
about 96 1/2% carbon dioxide,

00:09:12.620 --> 00:09:17.310
which has set up what's sometimes
called greenhouse gone wild

00:09:17.310 --> 00:09:19.440
on Venus, okay?

00:09:19.440 --> 00:09:22.970
And what that means
is that that thick,

00:09:22.970 --> 00:09:26.010
dense carbon dioxide
atmosphere is driving

00:09:26.010 --> 00:09:29.810
like a pressure cooker
environment down on the surface.

00:09:29.810 --> 00:09:34.840
So the surface temperatures are
about 860 degrees Farenheit.

00:09:34.840 --> 00:09:36.960
Let that sink in for just a second.

00:09:36.960 --> 00:09:38.820
That is hot enough to melt lead.

00:09:38.820 --> 00:09:42.410
It pretty much melts
anything except for titanium.

00:09:42.410 --> 00:09:44.240
It's incredibly hot.

00:09:44.240 --> 00:09:47.960
It also has air pressures,
about 92%,

00:09:47.960 --> 00:09:50.210 position:56%
92 times what we feel here on Earth.

00:09:50.210 --> 00:09:52.440
So imagine when you're about
half a mile underwater,

00:09:52.440 --> 00:09:55.290
that weight of the column of water
on top of you, that's what it feels

00:09:55.290 --> 00:09:59.030
like on the surface of Venus,
what it would feel like.

00:10:00.080 --> 00:10:04.970
At the top of the atmosphere, there
are hurricane force winds blowing

00:10:04.970 --> 00:10:10.970
around the planet about 250 miles
per hour, 100 meters per second

00:10:10.970 --> 00:10:13.080
at the top of the clouds.

00:10:13.080 --> 00:10:15.630
We don't really understand
what drives those winds.

00:10:15.630 --> 00:10:17.070
Why do they super rotate?

00:10:17.070 --> 00:10:19.240
Why do they rotate so fast?

00:10:19.240 --> 00:10:20.570
Remember, the planet, the surface

00:10:20.570 --> 00:10:22.610
of the planet is rotating
really slowly.

00:10:22.610 --> 00:10:25.120
So those winds are moving
about 60 times faster

00:10:25.120 --> 00:10:27.270
than the planet itself is rotating.

00:10:27.270 --> 00:10:29.390
Why? How do you do that?

00:10:29.390 --> 00:10:31.720
How do you describe,
if you're into physics,

00:10:31.720 --> 00:10:34.990
how do you describe the
momentum transfer that happens

00:10:34.990 --> 00:10:37.150
between the surface and the
atmosphere when they're behaving

00:10:37.150 --> 00:10:39.340
and moving so differently?

00:10:39.340 --> 00:10:42.630
We don't really know the
answer to that question.

00:10:42.630 --> 00:10:45.150
Down at the surface, as you
go down near the surface,

00:10:45.150 --> 00:10:47.900
those winds that are
racing at 250 miles per hour

00:10:47.900 --> 00:10:51.270
at the top are almost non-existent.

00:10:51.270 --> 00:10:53.190
Maybe two miles an hour, maybe.

00:10:53.190 --> 00:10:54.490
We don't really know.

00:10:54.490 --> 00:10:55.790
We don't have good data down low.

00:10:55.790 --> 00:10:57.090
But we know they're really low.

00:10:57.090 --> 00:10:59.720
There's not a lot of wind
on the surface at all.

00:10:59.720 --> 00:11:04.100
And that surface down there is this
carbon dioxide super critical fluid

00:11:04.100 --> 00:11:07.790
which doesn't really behave like
water or like a liquid or a gas.

00:11:07.790 --> 00:11:10.530
But you can imagine things on
