00:11:17.460 --> 00:11:22.780
To add to all of this fun and
excitement at Venus, if being hot

00:11:22.780 --> 00:11:25.890
and high pressure wasn't enough, to
get to the surface, you have to go

00:11:25.890 --> 00:11:32.410
through a 15-mile thick
layer of sulfuric acid.

00:11:32.410 --> 00:11:35.420
That's always fun.

00:11:35.420 --> 00:11:39.020
So that sulfuric acid
layer blocks most

00:11:39.020 --> 00:11:40.510
of the sunlight that
arrives at Venus.

00:11:40.510 --> 00:11:44.480 position:56%
So Venus is closer to the Sun than
Earth, so it gets a lot of sunlight.

00:11:44.480 --> 00:11:48.540
But 90% of that sunlight gets
absorbed as it passes through all

00:11:48.540 --> 00:11:51.370
of those clouds and this thick
carbon dioxide atmosphere.

00:11:51.370 --> 00:11:54.670
So by the time you get down
to the surface, only about 10%

00:11:54.670 --> 00:11:56.120
of the light gets through.

00:11:56.120 --> 00:12:00.000
This has been important when we're
