Yeah, there's a lot of different
ideas out there for terra forming

01:09:31.020 --> 01:09:34.440
or trying to make it a
more habitable place.

01:09:34.440 --> 01:09:36.920
Is there another question
maybe down here?

01:09:36.920 --> 01:09:38.220
Yeah?

01:09:38.220 --> 01:09:41.380
&gt;&gt; Do you know anything
about the size of the core

01:09:41.380 --> 01:09:43.640
and how it compares to Earth?

01:09:43.640 --> 01:09:45.470
&gt;&gt; Yeah, I think, again, I
think from my recollection,

01:09:45.470 --> 01:09:48.200
the core of Venus is more or
less the same size as Earth.

01:09:48.200 --> 01:09:51.140
So it's not that much
different in size.

01:09:51.140 --> 01:09:53.290
What we don't know,
though, is whether

01:09:53.290 --> 01:09:54.590
or not it's dynamically active.

01:09:54.590 --> 01:09:58.230
So at Earth, we have
what's called a dynamo,

01:09:58.230 --> 01:10:02.170
where we know that there's
convection going on, you know,

01:10:02.170 --> 01:10:05.620
outside of the core and in that
deepest part of the interior.

01:10:05.620 --> 01:10:11.650
And that causes the magnetic
field that we have here.

01:10:11.650 --> 01:10:13.970
Venus has no magnetic field,
has no magnetic field.

01:10:13.970 --> 01:10:15.470
So this is yet opening another
can of worms that I'll throw

01:10:15.470 --> 01:10:16.770
out there just for
your consideration.

01:10:16.770 --> 01:10:18.200
At Mars, we use the fact that
Mars doesn't have a magnetic field

01:10:18.200 --> 01:10:19.500
to explain why Mars
has no atmosphere,

01:10:19.500 --> 01:10:20.800
that the solar wind has
stripped off Mars's atmosphere,

01:10:20.800 --> 01:10:22.100
because it has no magnetic field.

01:10:22.100 --> 01:10:23.400
Well, what's happening at Venus?

01:10:23.400 --> 01:10:24.700
Venus has no magnetic field, and
it's got more atmosphere than any,

01:10:24.700 --> 01:10:26.000
you know, than Earth
and Mars combined.

01:10:26.000 --> 01:10:27.300
So how do you do that?

01:10:27.300 --> 01:10:28.600
So the core size I think
is fairly similar to Earth.

01:10:28.600 --> 01:10:29.900 position:56%
As I said, the densities, the masses
of the two planets are relatively,

01:10:29.900 --> 01:10:31.200
you know, on scale
with each other, right?

01:10:31.200 --> 01:10:32.500
Scaled. But there are other
differences between them

01:10:32.500 --> 01:10:33.800
that we don't understand.

